00:30:55.084 --> 00:30:57.250
That means that that company
is desperate to get rid

00:30:57.250 --> 00:30:58.040
of inventory.

00:30:58.040 --> 00:31:01.534
They must have modules stacking
up in their shipment yard.

00:31:01.534 --> 00:31:02.700
They're unable to move them.

00:31:02.700 --> 00:31:05.420
And so the chief financial
officer walks over and says,

00:31:05.420 --> 00:31:06.890
we got to get rid of this stuff.

00:31:06.890 --> 00:31:08.410
It's costing us money.

00:31:08.410 --> 00:31:11.250
It costs us money to keep
this product on the books.

00:31:11.250 --> 00:31:14.530
Sell it for whatever you have
to sell it for to get rid of it.

00:31:14.530 --> 00:31:17.560
And as a consequence, they
sell below cost, put it out

00:31:17.560 --> 00:31:20.050
into the market.

00:31:20.050 --> 00:31:22.270
And then you have
SolarWorld, or a US company,

00:31:22.270 --> 00:31:24.400
coming to the Department
of Commerce saying,

00:31:24.400 --> 00:31:26.160
they're dumping product.

00:31:26.160 --> 00:31:27.520
It's an unfair competition.

00:31:27.520 --> 00:31:29.270
According to the World
Trade Organization,

00:31:29.270 --> 00:31:32.230
you can't sell at a
price below your cost

00:31:32.230 --> 00:31:36.480
in order to squeeze out
and gain market share.

00:31:36.480 --> 00:31:39.500
So it's a complex
situation right now.

00:31:39.500 --> 00:31:43.000
I've described for you, in
as much detail as I can,

00:31:43.000 --> 00:31:46.170
